The importance of spirituality in supportive care.

Messina G(1), Anania S, Bonomo C, Veneroni L, Andreoli A, Mameli F, Ortolina C, 
De Fabritiis P, Gaffuri M, Imbesi F, Moja E.

Author information:
(1)Psychological Service, Foundation IRCCS Ospedale Maggiore Policlinico, Milan, 
Italy.

BACKGROUND: It has been shown that the pineal gland plays a fundamental role in 
mediating either the spiritual perception or the anticancer immunity by 
stimulating the endogenous production of anticancer cytokine interleukin (IL)-2.
OBJECTIVE: The present study was performed to evaluate the impact of a spiritual 
approach consisting of Kriya Yoga program alone or in association with melatonin 
(MLT) or low-dose IL-2 plus MLT on the survival time in a group of metastatic 
cancer patients with life expectancy less than 1 year.
MATERIALS AND METHODS: A case-control study was carried out in 240 patients 
(M/F: 146/94; median age: 62 years, range: 34-71, suffering from non-small-cell 
lung cancer or gastrointestinal tumors) who were subdivided into 6 groups of 40 
patients, treated with supportive care alone as a control group, supportive care 
